   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>170 8.7.8.7. with chorus.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Hymns, #697</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Weary pilgrim on life's pathway</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Struggling on beneath thy load</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Hear these words of consolation,</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>"Cast thy burden on the Lord."</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Chorus</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Cast thy burden on the Lord!</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Cast thy burden on the Lord,</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>And He will strengthen thee,</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>sustain and comfort thee</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Cast thy burden on the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Are thy tired feet unsteady?</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Does thy lamp no light afford?</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Is thy cross too great and heavy?</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>"Cast thy burden on the Lord."</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Are the ties of friendship severed?</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Hushed the voices fondly heard?</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Breaks thy heart with weight of anguish?</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>"Cast thy burden on the Lord."</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Does thy heart with faintness falter?</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Does thy mind forget His word?</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Does thy strength succumb to weakness?</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>"Cast thy burden on the Lord."</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>He will hold thee up from falling;</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>He will guide thy steps aright;</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>He will strengthen each endeavor;</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>He will keep thee by His might.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>171 8.7.8.7.D. with chorus.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Why grasp riches, harbor worry?</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>God's own servant will be fed;</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>If our God controls your outlays</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>You will not to drought be led.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>Daily new demands may threaten,</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>Daily He has fresh supply;</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>You are His endeared creation</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Trust His path, not asking why.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Chorus</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>Show your love and give your substance;</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Still some measure will remain.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>For your love and giving action,</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>God will bless and bless again.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>Trust!</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>More time you needn't borrow;</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>Though not fast, it is not slow.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>Trust!</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>The bottle will not empty;</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>From His means He will bestow.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>Though the lily may be naked,</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>Though the bird is short of aid,</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>Yet the flour for the widow</S>
   <S PAR='54' RSNT='1' SNO='54'>By her using didn't fade.</S>
   <S PAR='55' RSNT='1' SNO='55'>Why be anxious for tomorrow?</S>
   <S PAR='56' RSNT='1' SNO='56'>In your hand is what He gave.</S>
   <S PAR='57' RSNT='1' SNO='57'>Wherefore, try tomorrow's worries?</S>
   <S PAR='58' RSNT='1' SNO='58'>Thank your God for what you have.</S>
   <S PAR='59' RSNT='1' SNO='59'>Love is living, life is giving,</S>
   <S PAR='60' RSNT='1' SNO='60'>Spending doesn't wealth reduce.</S>
   <S PAR='61' RSNT='1' SNO='61'>When your small supply seems wasted,</S>
   <S PAR='62' RSNT='1' SNO='62'>Then God's blessing's more profuse.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
